summary: This is an email chain from May 21, 2020, among individuals with USANYS email addresses, coordinating a call scheduled for the next day regarding Epstein. The participants are discussing suitable times (11am or 1pm) for a meeting with 'the brass'.

events.title: Epstein Call Scheduled
events.description: A call is scheduled involving the email participants and 'the brass' to discuss Epstein-related matters.

keyFacts: The document is an email chain dated May 21, 2020, discussing scheduling a call about Epstein for the following day.
All participant email addresses are redacted and belong to the US Attorney's Office for the Southern District of New York (USANYS).
The call is to include 'the brass', indicating high-level officials or supervisors.
The email suggests ongoing Epstein-related work or coordination within the US Attorney's Office over a year after Epstein's death.
No specific individuals are named; all identifiers are redacted to email domains and roles like 'Contractor'.
